NEW YORK (AP) — Stocks around the world rallied on Friday as investors latched onto strands of hope about progress in the fight against the coronavirus.
The S&P 500 was up more than 1.5% in afternoon trading, following up on even bigger jumps in Europe and Asia.
Among the wisps of optimism that investors were focusing on Friday:— A news report cited early progress in a drug candidate for the virus.
(Photo: Ahn Young-joon, AP Photo)Together, the developments helped lift the S&P 500 by 1.7%, as of 3:15 p.m. Eastern time.
Bond yields drop when their prices rise, and investors tend to buy Treasurys when they’re worried about the economy.